 by examining the post-imperial soft power of the UK at the time of Brexit.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 4aFilm, Media & Cultural Studies. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / Direction & Production.2bisacsh1 aCooke, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDennison, Stephanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDwyer, Rachel, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aDwyer, Rachel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHigson, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHomewood, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHwee Lim, Song, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMeleiro, Alessandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNorris, Stephen M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaunders, Robert A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStrukov, Vlad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311078040640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147445629640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474456296423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474456296/original  a978-3-11-078040-6  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK